The paper deals with obfuscation techniques used for software security, specifically control-flow flattening. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the preservation of a specific security policy, which involves analyzing the behavior of the program, indicating a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper uses mathematical proofs to demonstrate the preservation of the security policy, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
